1
00:02:43,510 --> 00:02:45,580
This is the East Blue.

2
00:02:45,580 --> 00:02:49,720
The Revolutionary Army
has just freed Robin from slavery.

3
00:02:54,690 --> 00:02:57,060
The Light of the Revolution:

4
00:02:57,560 --> 00:03:03,430
we've called you that for ten years now,
ever since we started searching for you.

5
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:08,970
You are the sole survivor of Ohara,
the country that fought the world.

6
00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:15,070
If we ever found you, we are to protect you
from the government at any cost!

7
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:16,610
Orders from the boss.

8
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:18,880
Boss?

9
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,330
Commander in Chief of
the Revolutionary Army,

10
00:03:23,330 --> 00:03:24,520
Dragon.

11
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:27,220
Luffy's father...

12
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,720
Quite a twist of fate.

13
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,090
Again, I implore you...

14
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:38,560
Please accept a meeting with our boss.

15
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,030
We will be your escorts.

16
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:44,500
I can't. There is another place I must be.

17
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:47,870
Besides, I'll be fine without your protection.

18
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:52,010
Because I have my friends.

19
00:03:52,010 --> 00:03:55,350
You're referring to the Straw Hats, aren't you?

20
00:03:55,350 --> 00:04:00,850
Did you see this? Dragon's son,
Straw Hat Luffy, was in today's paper.

21
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:07,240
Yeah. They thought he vanished
after the war, yet here he is again.

22
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:10,700
Nico Robin needs to see
this article right away!

23
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,760
No doubt she's worried about him.

24
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:16,240
They'll still be out on the bridge.

25
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:20,640
We'll pass through many ghost towns
before the end of the bridge.

26
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:25,880
They were left behind as the people of this
country moved with the bridge's construction.

27
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:29,520
Incidentally, construction here
began 300 years ago.

28
00:04:30,150 --> 00:04:32,320
Why did they start building this bridge?

29
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:35,850
By decree of the world nobles,
the Celestial Dragons.

30
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:37,220
The Celestial Dragons?

31
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:40,190
Whatever reason they might have had,

32
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:44,000
it doesn't reduce the number
of people who died as slaves here!

33
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:46,970
Good work.

34
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,070
For you, Robin.

35
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:52,300
Luffy!

36
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:55,170
What a relief! You're safe.

37
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:00,380
What is it?

38
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:02,810
Did you see something interesting?

39
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,650
Yes.

40
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:29,740
This is Straw-boy's vanted poster, no?

41
00:05:29,740 --> 00:05:31,080
Yeah. Sure is.

42
00:05:31,610 --> 00:05:33,910
And Pirate Hunter Zoro's?

43
00:05:33,910 --> 00:05:34,780
Don't know him!

44
00:05:34,780 --> 00:05:37,520
And Cat Burgler Nami's?

45
00:05:39,150 --> 00:05:42,820
And this is the King of Snipers Sogeking's.

46
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:44,220
Yeah.

47
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:46,360
And this... is yours?

48
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:46,930
It's not!

49
00:05:46,930 --> 00:05:50,460
Then take a good look! I don't
see your poster anywhere!

50
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:54,170
If you're one of Straw-boy's men,
then vherre is the proof?!

51
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:56,570
But I am part of his crew!

52
00:05:56,570 --> 00:06:00,310
Just tell me what Luffy's
up to, you 'Kama King!

53
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:04,480
The newspaper said
you were working with Luffy!

54
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:06,180
Then this has to be you.

55
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:08,180
It's not...!

56
00:06:08,610 --> 00:06:11,950
It's not me, but... it is.

57
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:15,790
The name is mine.

58
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:22,260
Vhaat is this? A crisis of identity?

59
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:29,200
That's... me! That is me!

60
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:32,340
That disfigured wanted poster
is definitely mine!

61
00:06:32,340 --> 00:06:33,270
It's just...!

62
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:39,580
No. It looks nothing like you.

63
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,710
Then, don't make me say it!

64
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:43,520
I coughed up blood, you asshole!

65
00:06:43,850 --> 00:06:45,350
Vhaat a pickle.

66
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:50,920
Even if there is a 0.1 percent chance that you
might be a government or Marine spy,

67
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:57,300
my lips are sealed vhenn it comes
to information about Straw-boy!

68
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,930
I get that.

69
00:06:58,930 --> 00:07:00,570
Lend me a ship, then.

70
00:07:00,570 --> 00:07:03,370
I'm supposed to meet Luffy
at our rendezvous point.

71
00:07:03,370 --> 00:07:04,940
No ship for you.

72
00:07:05,540 --> 00:07:07,840
Then I'll just swim there!

73
00:07:08,140 --> 00:07:09,710
Vhaat are you saying?!

74
00:07:09,710 --> 00:07:13,050
Straw-boy vould indeed have
crewmates just as stubborn as he!

75
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:16,680
Then, it is settled.

76
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,080
You have touched my heart.

77
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:22,150
In honor of your passion,
I can tell vhaat happened to Straw-boy...

78
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:23,370
Yeah?

79
00:07:24,820 --> 00:07:28,900
Or not! Heehaw!

80
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:31,640
You're not telling?!
You really fooled us there!

81
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:33,330
Iva!

82
00:07:33,330 --> 00:07:34,400
Zip it, all of you!

83
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,870
Dammit...

84
00:07:38,870 --> 00:07:41,240
He seems pretty defeated, right?

85
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:45,340
Maybe now he'll finally be willing
to wear the Sweets dress!

86
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:48,410
I'll never wear that again! Back off!

87
00:07:49,180 --> 00:07:53,490
I'm a manly man who likes ladies!

88
00:07:53,490 --> 00:07:55,920
Stay away from me!

89
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,560
– Boo! Boo!
– Boo! Boo!

90
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:02,130
Hey, it was Iva, right?

91
00:08:02,130 --> 00:08:05,160
Since I'm a pirate, I'll just
take one of your ships.

92
00:08:06,130 --> 00:08:07,770
Let's have a duel.

93
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:09,670
Sounds great.

94
00:08:22,410 --> 00:08:26,620
I vill tell you vhaat Straw-boy
is doing, Twirly-boy.

95
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:29,760
Why the change of heart?

96
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:34,460
Because the whole voorld already knows.

97
00:08:34,460 --> 00:08:37,330
But who knows vhaat he is planning...?

98
00:08:37,830 --> 00:08:39,600
Is this today's paper?

99
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,230
Wha...?! Luffy!

100
00:08:41,530 --> 00:08:44,040
Iva, you have a call from Baltigo.

101
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:45,040
Really?

102
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:47,270
Please take it in the communications room.

103
00:08:48,170 --> 00:08:50,280
Because of the recent war,

104
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:54,610
the whole voorld learned who your son is, Dragon.

105
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:57,450
Are your revolutionaries
shocked by this news?

106
00:08:58,820 --> 00:09:02,390
If anything, they're relieved
to find out that their enigmatic boss

107
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:04,260
is a flesh-and-blood human being.

108
00:09:04,260 --> 00:09:06,160
Not that it matters.

109
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,890
Luffy is no longer a child.

110
00:09:07,890 --> 00:09:12,430
Still, I never would have imagined
a team-up between the two of you.

111
00:09:12,430 --> 00:09:15,970
An interesting tvisst of fate, no?

112
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:22,900
At any rate, Inazuma and I have
a mountain of qvestions for you,

113
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:25,940
and there is also our jailbreak report.

114
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:32,980
All in due time. Soon, the various
world leaders will be called to assembly.

115
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:38,660
Whitebeard's death will change the government
regime and the course of the world.

116
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:43,560
Also, I need to tell you about Kuma's fate.

117
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:46,730
Yes, I vaant to know the details of that.

118
00:09:46,730 --> 00:09:50,740
Vhyy is he now a government stooge?

119
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:54,070
The Kuma I knew is gone.

120
00:09:54,470 --> 00:09:57,940
He vass trying to kill me.

121
00:09:58,410 --> 00:10:01,650
By the vayy, Dragon, have you
seen today's newspaper?

122
00:10:01,650 --> 00:10:05,050
Straw-boy is just full of surprises!

123
00:10:05,050 --> 00:10:07,720
He is as unpredictable as his father.

124
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:11,660
I cannot believe he vould do something
like that at Marineford, of all places!

125
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:19,560
Meanwhile, at the Thousand Sunny's berth...

126
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:22,730
On the Grand Line at Sabaody Archipelago...

127
00:10:22,730 --> 00:10:25,670
Grove #44.

128
00:10:25,670 --> 00:10:29,140
Hand that ship over to us!

129
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:35,080
It belongs to Straw Hat Luffy,
the son of Dragon the Revolutionary, right?!

130
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:39,280
I'm sure the Marines will
give us a hefty reward for it!

131
00:10:41,990 --> 00:10:43,960
We're both in the same business,

132
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:48,490
so I'm willing to share the profits
with you if you hand it over.

133
00:10:48,860 --> 00:10:50,760
How about it, Flying Fish Riders?

134
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:52,260
What's that? I'm handsome?

135
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,730
Are you deaf?! Just give us
the ship, dumbass!

136
00:10:57,070 --> 00:10:59,970
I ain't givin' you guys shit!

137
00:11:06,010 --> 00:11:09,850
Pay attention, you guys!
This handsome man is Duval.

138
00:11:09,850 --> 00:11:12,650
I won't let you scoundrels take the ladies–

139
00:11:13,390 --> 00:11:15,620
I mean, take the ship, as long as I'm sexy–

140
00:11:15,990 --> 00:11:17,390
I mean, as long as I'm here!

141
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:20,290
You messed up your speech!

142
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:25,100
As long as there is life in my eyes, you will
never touch the young master's ship!

143
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:27,600
Touch it, and I'll touch a pretty lady–

144
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,100
Ah, I got that wrong!

145
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:32,470
I mean, you can't touch it!

146
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:34,140
Ain't that right, men?!

147
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:35,410
– Yes, Rose-some!
– Yes, Rose-some!

148
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,210
Retreat!

149
00:11:39,910 --> 00:11:42,050
Duval, you're so cool!

150
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:46,420
A lady's declaration
of love for handsome me?

151
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:52,090
I-I love you too!

152
00:11:52,090 --> 00:11:56,660
I think I'll show them the Mermaid
Cafe first. It's very trendy!

153
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:01,870
But Camie, Fishman Island's finest
attraction is the Fishman Karate Dojo.

154
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:05,700
I promised the bone dude I'd
introduce him to the mermaid princess!

155
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:08,610
Boss Duval, she won't acknowledge you!

156
00:12:08,610 --> 00:12:10,910
True, but it's cool!

157
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:15,510
Hey, Shakky? The vivre card
will lead them all back here, right?

158
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:19,620
And thanks to that article today,
now we know Luffy's okay.

159
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:24,160
Yes. It might not be for awhile, but...

160
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:27,390
at least Ray safely met up
with our little Monkey.

161
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:34,500
Until they come back,
we must protect this ship.

162
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:37,640
No problem 'cause
that's where we come in, Sis!

163
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:40,310
Even if the Marines come a-knockin',

164
00:12:40,310 --> 00:12:44,080
there ain't nobody gonna steal this ship!

165
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:46,480
I'm counting on you.

166
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:52,780
Boss Duval! Bad news!
It's Kuma! He's like a hulking bear!

167
00:12:53,220 --> 00:12:56,390
A bear?! There ain't no bears on this island!

168
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:57,690
That's...!

169
00:13:05,130 --> 00:13:08,400
It's Bartholomew Kuma of the Seven Warlords!

170
00:13:24,050 --> 00:13:25,750
Don't panic.

171
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:29,450
This man spoke with Ray a little while ago.

172
00:13:30,890 --> 00:13:32,760
He's an ally.

173
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:34,260
Right?

174
00:13:40,870 --> 00:13:44,870
This is Sandy Island on the Grand Line...

175
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:47,440
a country of sand,
the Kingdom of Alabasta...

176
00:13:48,510 --> 00:13:51,180
In the capital city of Alubarna.

177
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,580
What's the situation with the pirates?

178
00:13:56,580 --> 00:13:59,520
We chased them off.
The city suffered minimal damage.

179
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:03,150
We are increasing security
at every port in the nation.

180
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:04,990
We cannot lower our guard.

181
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:09,730
I wish all pirates were like Luffy and his crew,

182
00:14:09,730 --> 00:14:11,660
but that just isn't the case.

183
00:14:12,230 --> 00:14:14,130
Speaking of which, Your Majesty...

184
00:14:14,130 --> 00:14:16,270
did you see the newspaper this morning?

185
00:14:16,270 --> 00:14:18,000
Oh, of course.

186
00:14:20,410 --> 00:14:25,380
What are those on Luffy's arm?
Those numbers... Rather those markings?

187
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:27,710
Or is it just to look cool?

188
00:14:27,710 --> 00:14:30,180
No, that's not like Luffy...

189
00:14:38,260 --> 00:14:43,830
Now, on the Grand Line,
on a certain island, in a certain town...

190
00:14:47,530 --> 00:14:51,340
H-Hey! What is he doing on this island?!

191
00:14:51,340 --> 00:14:52,600
Shh! He'll hear us!

192
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:56,710
It's only been three weeks since the war.

193
00:14:57,940 --> 00:15:00,650
He barely escaped with his life...

194
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:07,250
so then what's his game?

195
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,910
He must have some ulterior motive.

196
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:11,720
If not, then he's lost his mind.

197
00:15:12,890 --> 00:15:14,830
You think so, Daz?

198
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:21,970
Straw Hat was wounded. Wounds like that
don't heal so easily, wouldn't you say?

199
00:15:23,330 --> 00:15:26,970
Touché, you bastard.
Honing that wit of yours, huh?

200
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,710
My wounds have long since healed,

201
00:15:32,410 --> 00:15:37,350
and to prove it, I'll soon revisit the New World
for a nostalgic trip down memory lane.

202
00:15:38,850 --> 00:15:40,220
Care to join?

203
00:15:42,590 --> 00:15:43,890
Indeed.

204
00:15:45,060 --> 00:15:48,460
On a certain deserted island
on the Grand Line...

205
00:15:53,330 --> 00:15:55,770
Ever since you were arrested,

206
00:15:55,770 --> 00:15:59,700
I stayed up every night sick with worry
and hatching plans to break you out!

207
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:04,580
We sailed far and wide,
racking up battle scars at every turn!

208
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:09,050
And then the newspaper said our imprisoned
captain had suddenly become a war hero!

209
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,650
Captain Buggy!

210
00:16:15,650 --> 00:16:17,420
We looked so hard for you!

211
00:16:19,090 --> 00:16:23,390
We've always trusted and followed you,
so we thought to ourselves,

212
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:27,070
"Do you see that, New World?!
That's our captain!"

213
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:31,700
Y-You guys! You really had
that much faith in me?!

214
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,940
I've really missed you all!

215
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:36,270
– Captain Buggy!
– Captain Buggy!

216
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:44,450
Didn't you guys...

217
00:16:44,890 --> 00:16:47,390
abandon Buggy?

218
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:01,130
Look here, you bottom feeders!

219
00:17:02,430 --> 00:17:06,070
I am First Mate Mohji of the Buggy Pirates!

220
00:17:06,070 --> 00:17:08,640
– First Mate Mohji!
– First Mate Mohji!

221
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:11,910
And I'm First Officer Cabaji!

222
00:17:11,910 --> 00:17:14,650
– First Officer Cabaji!
– First Officer Cabaji!

223
00:17:14,650 --> 00:17:19,250
And this is my partner, Richie!

224
00:17:20,150 --> 00:17:22,890
Richie!

225
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:30,560
Hard to believe all that stuff
in the newspaper is true!

226
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:35,430
They're all notorious criminals with
high bounties. I've seen the wanted posters.

227
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:41,310
Makes sense! They're heinous inmates
from Impel Down, after all!

228
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:42,980
Oh, right!

229
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:47,110
Hey, Alvida, want to see something amazing?

230
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:48,950
Ta-da!

231
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:51,520
Isn't this...

232
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:55,320
I can't believe it!
Captain John's treasure mark?!

233
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:56,550
Indeed it is!

234
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:59,890
This is incredible! How'd you
get your hands on it?!

235
00:18:00,530 --> 00:18:04,570
That Straw Hat kid had it with him!

236
00:18:06,260 --> 00:18:09,800
The winds of this world aren't
blowing to the west or east.

237
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:13,140
They're all blowing in my direction!

238
00:18:15,140 --> 00:18:16,240
Hey, Buggy!

239
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:21,550
A carrier bat just brought you
a message from the government!

240
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:23,410
Huh?! How'd they know I was here?!

241
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:26,480
This is...

242
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:30,220
indeed an astonishing message!

243
00:18:30,220 --> 00:18:32,420
Don't go and read it before I do!

244
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:38,230
I swear, this man inevitably
comes up in our discussions.

245
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:43,230
Although, it isn't so surprising considering
Straw Hat Luffy is Garp's grandson.

246
00:18:43,230 --> 00:18:47,210
What is his connection to Rayleigh?

247
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:50,480
I doubt that man wants to retake center stage.

248
00:18:51,140 --> 00:18:53,850
Jinbe finally turned against us as well.

249
00:18:53,850 --> 00:18:59,080
His position in the Seven Warlords
was a sign of peace between our species.

250
00:18:59,080 --> 00:19:00,620
How unfortunate.

251
00:19:00,620 --> 00:19:04,860
The three great powers are
completely out of balance now.

252
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:08,490
How should we fill the three vacancies
in the Seven Warlords of the Sea?

253
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:11,960
We should allow things to develop
further in the New World.

254
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:15,670
The balance of power between pirates
will undoubtedly shift as well.

255
00:19:15,670 --> 00:19:19,140
We must recruit only
the most powerful of them.

256
00:19:19,140 --> 00:19:23,440
Blackbeard has already made
his move in the New World.

257
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:29,000
He took out one of the rookies
worth over 100 million.

258
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:33,820
After all, he knows Whitebeard's
territory like the back of his hand.

259
00:19:35,190 --> 00:19:40,660
This gives him a veritable head start in the race
to become the newest of the Four Emperors.

260
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:47,200
A human who has eaten two devil fruits...
There exists no historical precedent!

261
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:50,600
The only ones who could possibly stop him...

262
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,340
are the Four Emperors.

263
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:57,480
There is also Marco the Phoenix
or the other remnants of Whitebeard's crew.

264
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:01,750
Then there is the ever troublesome "D."

265
00:20:01,750 --> 00:20:03,920
Portgas was one of them too.

266
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:09,050
These days, that name is
showing up a little too often.

267
00:20:12,620 --> 00:20:17,960
I tried to talk him out of it,
but Garp has all but resigned.

268
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:23,560
But he will keep his title
and remain in the Marines...

269
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:27,490
in order to educate Marine greenhorns.

270
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:33,240
If you intend to resign as Marine Fleet Admiral,
can you at least make the same concession,

271
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:35,010
Sengoku?

272
00:20:35,010 --> 00:20:35,900
Very well.

273
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:39,050
I accept your request.

274
00:20:39,050 --> 00:20:41,920
It might be a nice way to spend retirement.

275
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:49,660
The two of you have led the Marines
from the front since Roger's era...

276
00:20:49,660 --> 00:20:54,600
Your departure from the battlefield
will make quite the splash.

277
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:59,870
Taking into account all the escapees
from Impel Down Level 6,

278
00:20:59,870 --> 00:21:03,780
there are a lot of legendary
pirates still out there.

279
00:21:05,110 --> 00:21:08,680
Newgate was the greatest of them all.

280
00:21:10,620 --> 00:21:14,190
With a new era of piracy
just on the horizon,

281
00:21:14,190 --> 00:21:18,120
old-timers like us shouldn't
be leading the Marines.

282
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:21,890
"Justice" does not transcend generations.
It reflects the values of an era.

283
00:21:24,060 --> 00:21:26,130
It pains me to hear you say this.

284
00:21:26,130 --> 00:21:31,270
Anyway, Grand Admiral Kong, as for
who will be the next Fleet Admiral,

285
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:34,310
allow me to recommend Aokiji for the position.

286
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:37,810
So he survived.

287
00:21:37,810 --> 00:21:39,480
Pretty impressive.

288
00:21:40,380 --> 00:21:44,320
Hear the latest? Straw Hat
went and caused another scene.

289
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:45,280
Yeah.

290
00:21:45,290 --> 00:21:50,990
"My Marine Motto: Lazy Justice"

291
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:50,990
The great war just barely ended,
and now the sixteen tolls of the bell...?

292
00:21:50,990 --> 00:21:53,320
Could this be some kind of message?

293
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:56,830
Who knows?

294
00:21:56,830 --> 00:21:59,500
Anyway, is there word on my transfer?

295
00:22:00,030 --> 00:22:03,840
Ah, I'll need to bring it up
to Fleet Admiral Sengoku,

296
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:05,900
but are you serious?

297
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:09,170
I'm not the type to crack jokes.

298
00:22:09,170 --> 00:22:15,510
Right, of course, but people aren't
exactly lining up to get stationed at G-5.

299
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:18,280
That place is just full of problems.

300
00:22:19,650 --> 00:22:23,250
Branch 5 of the Grand Line's Marine forces.

301
00:22:23,860 --> 00:22:26,720
That means you wanna go
to the New World, huh?

302
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:30,760
I'd like to keep my targets close.

303
00:22:32,610 --> 00:22:35,730
It's a power called haki...

304
00:22:35,730 --> 00:22:38,340
There's no doubt this is one of its forms.

305
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:43,440
The shock of battle must've somehow
awakened this power within you.

306
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:48,280
Under normal circumstances, it will
only develop after extensive training.

307
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:51,550
Haki... This...?!

308
00:22:51,550 --> 00:22:55,950
All Marine officers ranked
vice admiral or higher can use it.

309
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:56,790
Seriously?

310
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:59,820
I can feel the presence
of other people so strongly...

311
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:01,160
It's just too much!

312
00:23:01,660 --> 00:23:04,100
You two are Garp's apprentices, right?

313
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,130
He'll teach you all about it!

314
00:23:06,130 --> 00:23:07,900
Hey, doctor!

315
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:10,000
Will I learn it too?

316
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,440
Not a clue.

317
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:18,510
Damn it! It feels like you're
a step ahead of me now!

318
00:23:18,510 --> 00:23:21,310
I don't even know how it happened...

319
00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:24,620
This is inconceivable!

320
00:23:25,220 --> 00:23:30,120
During this Summit War, we discovered
he was the sworn brother of Portgas D. Ace,

321
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:32,590
the son of Dragon the Revolutionary,

322
00:23:32,590 --> 00:23:38,150
and last, but not least, the grandchild
of our very own Vice Admiral Garp!

323
00:23:38,150 --> 00:23:41,070
The pirate, Monkey D. Luffy!

324
00:23:41,730 --> 00:23:48,040
He went missing after the war,
but sure enough, he survived!

325
00:23:48,970 --> 00:23:51,610
He suddenly reappeared
at Marine Headquarters!

326
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,810
Sink that warship!

327
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:06,120
No way... Is that the living legend,

328
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:09,130
former first mate of the Roger Pirates,

329
00:24:09,130 --> 00:24:11,530
the Dark King, Silvers Rayleigh?!

330
00:24:25,940 --> 00:24:28,150
They've gone once around the island...

331
00:24:28,150 --> 00:24:30,880
It's like a funeral at sea!

332
00:24:42,630 --> 00:24:45,100
Concentrate fire from all directions!

333
00:25:05,350 --> 00:25:06,920
Now, go wild!

334
00:25:08,090 --> 00:25:08,750
Right!

335
00:25:10,220 --> 00:25:12,390
Capture Straw Hat!

336
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:16,260
Gum-Gum Whip!

337
00:25:24,970 --> 00:25:27,510
What's he doing at the Ox Bell?!

338
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:06,310
This will make a great shot!

339
00:26:28,930 --> 00:26:30,500
After him! Don't let him escape!

340
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:32,700
Now he's leaving...

341
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,870
What was that all about?

342
00:26:34,870 --> 00:26:38,710
The Dark King Rayleigh,
and Jinbe of the Seven Warlords...

343
00:26:38,710 --> 00:26:40,380
They're with Straw Hat?!

344
00:26:40,380 --> 00:26:43,610
Rayleigh was on the Pirate King's crew.

345
00:26:43,610 --> 00:26:46,120
Does that mean Straw Hat
is Roger's successor?!

346
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:50,620
H-Hold on! But Straw Hat is Dragon's son!
There must be some mistake...

347
00:26:51,390 --> 00:26:52,860
In any case, this...

348
00:26:53,490 --> 00:26:55,060
is big news!

349
00:27:14,380 --> 00:27:17,520
People all around the world
have already seen this article!

350
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:22,190
They're reading how we let Straw Hat
slip through our fingers!

351
00:27:22,190 --> 00:27:23,590
How humiliating!

352
00:27:23,590 --> 00:27:26,660
If we try to interpret Straw Hat's actions,

353
00:27:26,660 --> 00:27:32,660
it's likely a memorial to his brother, to Whitebeard,
and to the rest who fell during the war.

354
00:27:32,660 --> 00:27:35,730
He circled the island and then
gave a moment of silence.

355
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:40,100
However, the bell would
only ring twice on such occasions.

356
00:27:40,100 --> 00:27:41,910
Yet he rung it sixteen times!

357
00:27:41,910 --> 00:27:46,740
Sixteen rings... This is likely a challenge to us!

358
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:51,080
Upon the waters of the Grand Line...

359
00:27:52,380 --> 00:27:55,320
Sorry about making you guys
come all this way.

360
00:27:55,320 --> 00:27:57,890
It's fine. We're used to going on expeditions.

361
00:27:57,890 --> 00:27:59,790
What're you doing over there?

362
00:27:59,790 --> 00:28:02,390
We're keeping an eye on your well being.

363
00:28:02,390 --> 00:28:04,660
It's an order from the Snake Princess.

364
00:28:04,660 --> 00:28:09,000
The Snake Princess got
too excited earlier and collapsed.

365
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:13,270
So now we're closely monitoring you.

366
00:28:15,770 --> 00:28:19,610
I really hope those guys get the message...

367
00:28:20,610 --> 00:28:23,050
They'll get it if they see the article.

368
00:28:23,050 --> 00:28:26,220
It's out of the ordinary for you; that's the key.

369
00:28:26,220 --> 00:28:27,450
Hey, stop that!

370
00:28:27,450 --> 00:28:31,160
There was one man who
seemed rather dense, though.

371
00:28:31,190 --> 00:28:33,390
Well, I'm sure he'll
figure it out somehow.

372
00:28:34,020 --> 00:28:36,630
They'll all figure it out.

373
00:28:36,630 --> 00:28:38,530
I just know it.

374
00:28:39,530 --> 00:28:41,730
In the sky above the Grand Line...

375
00:28:47,070 --> 00:28:50,170
So that's it! I got it, Luffy!

376
00:28:51,310 --> 00:28:55,210
I understand! I really do!
I got it! I got it!

377
00:28:55,950 --> 00:28:59,620
Atop the colossal bridge in the East Blue...

378
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,290
Understood. That's just the way it is.

379
00:29:07,290 --> 00:29:10,630
What is it, Robin?

380
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:15,930
Aye aye, Luffy.

381
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,870
The Kamabakka Queendom...

382
00:29:29,050 --> 00:29:32,120
I read you loud and clear, Luffy.

383
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:33,420
Vhaat is it?

384
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:40,420
The ruins of Muggy Kingdom...

385
00:29:41,130 --> 00:29:44,360
Hey, are you done reading it?
My hands are getting tired.

386
00:29:44,900 --> 00:29:46,730
Just hang on...!

387
00:29:46,730 --> 00:29:48,330
What's the catch...?

388
00:29:48,330 --> 00:29:51,640
Luffy wouldn't do something like this!

389
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:55,070
This had to be Rayleigh's idea
since he was with him!

390
00:29:55,070 --> 00:29:56,970
There's definitely something to this...!

391
00:29:57,910 --> 00:30:01,180
In Futureland Baldimore...

392
00:30:05,050 --> 00:30:07,080
Up we go...!

393
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:10,450
Man, that sure took it outta me!

394
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:12,820
Old guy!

395
00:30:28,610 --> 00:30:29,710
I see!

396
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,580
The Bowin Archipelago...

397
00:30:36,580 --> 00:30:39,360
What is it now'n, Usopp'n?

398
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:41,050
I understand, Luffy!

399
00:30:44,660 --> 00:30:47,490
The Sky Island of Weatheria...

400
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:51,900
I get it.

401
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:53,260
But really,

402
00:30:53,260 --> 00:30:56,770
this decision of yours doesn't
factor in how we might feel at all!

403
00:30:56,770 --> 00:30:59,800
Young lady! They're gonna catch you!

404
00:31:01,210 --> 00:31:03,410
The Kingdom of Armsolong...

405
00:31:13,580 --> 00:31:17,120
It's almost showtime! Try and look lively.

406
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:18,290
Here.

407
00:31:20,460 --> 00:31:21,690
Luffy!

408
00:31:21,690 --> 00:31:27,600
Thanks for your patience! Behold!
It's the world's only walking skeleton!

409
00:31:34,300 --> 00:31:36,940
Oh, is that so?

410
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:41,610
I understand, Luffy.

411
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:50,450
News of Straw Hat Luffy's latest actions
races to all corners of the world.

412
00:31:51,420 --> 00:31:54,660
Even here, in the New World...

413
00:31:54,660 --> 00:31:58,130
So Straw Hat Luffy made it out alive, huh?

414
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:02,700
"Sixteen bells at Marineford to ring in the new era."

415
00:32:03,730 --> 00:32:05,140
What even is the Ox Bell?

416
00:32:07,070 --> 00:32:08,870
The Ox Bell is...

417
00:32:09,870 --> 00:32:12,310
a sacred bell once mounted on a certain warship:

418
00:32:12,310 --> 00:32:15,780
the Ox Lloyds, which served the Marines long ago.

419
00:32:16,750 --> 00:32:21,590
To herald the coming year, it's rung
eight times as thanks for the passing year,

420
00:32:21,590 --> 00:32:23,940
and another eight as a prayer for the next.

421
00:32:25,020 --> 00:32:29,090
Thus, ringing the bell sixteen
times is a Marine tradition.

422
00:32:29,090 --> 00:32:31,260
That's the meaning of sixteen tolls.

423
00:32:33,230 --> 00:32:35,570
But it's too early in the year for that.

424
00:32:35,570 --> 00:32:40,040
Instead, this indicates he rang the bell
to declare the beginning of a new era.

425
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:46,840
So he's saying, "Whitebeard's era is over,
and I will create a new one," huh?

426
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:51,280
If that's not his intent,
why go back to the place...

427
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:54,750
where he'd relive the pain
of losing his brother?

428
00:32:56,450 --> 00:32:58,790
He pisses me off!

429
00:32:58,790 --> 00:33:05,790
Because of the war, he really stands out from
all the rookies with bounties over 100 million!

430
00:33:05,790 --> 00:33:11,270
But I'm not so weak that I'd
let him stay ahead for long!

431
00:33:13,970 --> 00:33:18,980
I had expected more from this New World.

432
00:33:18,980 --> 00:33:21,380
What's with these weaklings?!

433
00:33:21,380 --> 00:33:23,150
Please, give us a break!

434
00:33:23,150 --> 00:33:25,950
Nobody here did anything to harm you!

435
00:33:25,950 --> 00:33:29,120
We were just about to leave these waters!

436
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:31,320
Let us return to Paradise alive!

437
00:33:31,890 --> 00:33:35,430
Paradise? Back to your
warm and cozy homes?

438
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:37,950
You guys only just came to this sea,

439
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:41,130
so you don't know how terrifying it truly is!

440
00:33:48,710 --> 00:33:49,940
Straw Hat?

441
00:33:49,940 --> 00:33:52,540
That's right. He's making waves yet again.

442
00:33:52,540 --> 00:33:55,010
Don't get in a flap about it.

443
00:33:55,010 --> 00:33:58,750
Only the one who calls checkmate is the winner.

444
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:01,080
What was that?!

445
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:03,390
Father! The ship...

446
00:34:03,390 --> 00:34:06,260
It's up off the water and floating to the sky!

447
00:34:06,260 --> 00:34:08,030
What?!

448
00:34:08,030 --> 00:34:11,260
What's the big deal?!
How is this happening?!

449
00:34:11,260 --> 00:34:12,760
Get us back on course!

450
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:15,200
Father! Something's coming from above!

451
00:34:18,700 --> 00:34:22,070
No, wait! We're the ones
being sucked toward it!

452
00:34:27,910 --> 00:34:29,810
I am truly sorry.

453
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:34,280
Could you please repeat that?

454
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:36,490
I couldn't quite hear you.

455
00:34:36,490 --> 00:34:38,290
I'm Brownbeard!

456
00:34:38,290 --> 00:34:42,930
I'm a pirate with a bounty of over
80 million: the great Brownbeard!

457
00:34:43,590 --> 00:34:47,660
You'd best remember
my name! This is my turf!

458
00:34:47,660 --> 00:34:50,930
This is an awful thing you've
done to my dear underlings.

459
00:34:50,930 --> 00:34:53,200
I'm gonna take it out of your hide!

460
00:34:53,200 --> 00:34:58,480
I see. Your name was so utterly
ridiculous, I thought I'd misheard.

461
00:34:58,910 --> 00:35:00,650
Let me make two things clear.

462
00:35:00,650 --> 00:35:03,180
First, I hate jokes.

463
00:35:03,180 --> 00:35:04,350
Jokes?!

464
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:06,680
As for the other other thing...

465
00:35:08,420 --> 00:35:12,390
the shadow of death
looms over you on this day.

466
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:25,140
Is the log pose really
pointing toward that island?

467
00:35:25,140 --> 00:35:28,980
Lightning is striking the island like rain!

468
00:35:28,980 --> 00:35:30,970
This is insane!

469
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:39,320
How do we make it ashore?!

470
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:44,920
Bold men who set foot into the
New World for the first time...

471
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:48,390
High Priest! Someone's coming!

472
00:35:49,530 --> 00:35:50,530
Who is that?

473
00:35:50,530 --> 00:35:55,470
...all say the same thing about
the first half of the Grand Line...

474
00:35:55,470 --> 00:35:57,930
Greetings, young 'uns.

475
00:35:58,440 --> 00:36:01,140
Who's the old bag?

476
00:36:01,140 --> 00:36:05,240
..."That ocean was Paradise!"

477
00:36:07,180 --> 00:36:10,690
Need an umbrella?

478
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:14,820
If we stay on this sea, we won't last.
No matter how many lives we have!

479
00:36:14,820 --> 00:36:19,060
We just wanna go back to Paradise! Please!

480
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:22,060
You make me sick.

481
00:36:23,730 --> 00:36:28,830
Anyone who doesn't have
the resolve to risk their lives

482
00:36:28,830 --> 00:36:33,570
has no place... on this sea!

483
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:41,650
I'll take the lead in no time at all!

484
00:36:41,650 --> 00:36:46,480
So watch your back and wait, Straw Hat!

485
